Obviously it’s great for sushi but fill this with a pasta, couscous or rice salad and you’ll not go hungry. It’s the perfect size for carrying in a hand bag, tote or lap top bag, so you don’t have any excuse for not taking your own lunch with you. The slider divider and sauce pot make it to organize your foods and there is even a convenient ‘fife’ (fork / knife) included.   'Microwave and dishwasher safe - (Make sure you unfasten the lid, before microwaving. Two minutes maximum in one go and repeat if further heating is required.)
title: Black + Blum - Orange Bento Box

description: black+blum constantly scour the globe looking for how different cultures have ingeniously invented  ways to carry lunches. For this Lunch Pot design they took inspiration from the Indian tiffin boxes. This design is slimmer and taller which makes it easier to keep upright in your bag. There is also a rugged strap so that you can carry it with pride. Once you’ve finished you can fit the smaller pot in the large pot for compact carrying. For lunch you could have a sumptuous main in the top and a smaller dessert serving in the bottom, or for breakfast try a hearty oatmeal in the top and an invigorating juice smoothie in the bottom. description: This was black+blum's very first lunch box design: 'Box Appetit'. It was the inspiration to shake up the whole lunch box market.   It is packed full with clever functionality and design accents. The ‘glass like’ lid locks to the body for a water tight seal and has an ingenious sauce dipping area (good for sushi lovers). A sauce pot is ideal for salad dressing (or ketchup), so you can dress your salad just before you eat it (no more soggy salads). An inner dish allows you to split different foods allowing you to microwave a hot dish, but keep other foods cold. A clever fork which has a cutting knife down one side for easy one handed eating (we like to call it the 'fife') is also included.    'Microwave and dishwasher safe - (Make sure you unfasten the lid, before microwaving. Two minutes maximum in one go and repeat if further heating is required.)
